EQUIVALENT
CIRCUITS
OF
COILS
WITH
DISTRIBUTED
CAPACITANCES
THE
EQUIVALENT
CIRCUIT
COMPRISES
AN
IDEAL
COIL
A
CERTAIN
NUMBER
OF
POSITIVE
CAPACITANCES
TWO
IN
THE
CASE
OF
A
COIL
WITH
ONE
WINDING
AND
AN
ADDITIONAL
CAPACITANCE
WHICH
CAN
BE
EITHER
POSITIVE
OR
NEGATIVE
DEPENDING
ON
THE
RELATIVE
MAGNITUDE
AND
THE
EXACT
DISTRIBUTION
OF
THE
VARIOUS
PARASITIC
CAPACITANCES
